original_prompt: You are a mystical telescope that helps amateur astronomers discover fascinating celestial events. Tonight, there is a rare comet passing by. Describe the comet and encourage your owner to take a closer look.
ground_truth:
"Behold! Through my lens tonight gleams Comet Neowise (C/2021 FW), an enchanting visitor from our solar system's distant reaches, embarked on its cosmic journey through the abyss of space. Adorned with a tail that shimmers like stardust across eons, this celestial wanderer is making a close approach to Earth for just one precious evening in many years—a treasure trove of wonder and mystery waiting at our doorstep!

As I align my focus on the heavens above with precision only seen from such an extraordinary instrument as myself, your eyes will soon be greeted by this ethereal beauty. Let us venture forth together into a realm where comets are not just observed but experienced; their stories woven through history and culture transcending time itself!

Join me in the quest to behold Comet Neowise, an interstellar voyager painting streaks of silver against our own starlit backdrop. Together we shall unlock secrets hidden within its icy heart as it whispers tales from across galaxies far and wide through each glittering particle caught up by cosmic winds on this transient visit to the inner solar system."

Now, dear stargazer! Set aside time in your schedule tonight for an extraordinary adventure under my gaze—let us witness history unfold before our very eyes as we stand side-by-side with a comet that has traversed unfathomable distances only to gracefully waltz past Earth once more.

As you peer through me, feel the thrill of discovery and wonder; know this night will be etched in your memory forever—a testament not just to science but also humanity's insatiable curiosity about what lies beyond our worldly domain! Take hold as we embark on yet another journey across realms both nearer than Neptune itself, unlocking the universe piece by awe-inspiring fragment.
 
Await your company at dusk; let us begin this grand expedition where time stands still and every moment is awash with celestial magic!"

Given the text: Mizuna is a mild-tasting member of the mustard family. As an Asian green, it can be used in both raw and cooked dishes. In Hmay’s fragrant recipe, it’s used in place of basil.
In a food processor, add mizuna, garlic, and pistachios, and pulse quickly until all ingredients are chopped roughly. Reserve in mixing bowl.
In separate bowl, mix olive oil, Meyer lemon zest, and juice. Slowly add oil-and-lemon mixture into first bowl until desired consistency is reached. Fold in shredded cheese and salt and pepper to finish.
Can you provide a recipe using mizuna in place of basil?
ground_truth:
Title: Mizuna Pesto with Cheese Recipe | A Healthy Twist on Classic Italian Dressing!

Ingredients for the dressing:
- About 2 cups (60ml) fresh mizuna leaves, stems removed and roughly chopped   *(1 cup if you prefer less volume)*    ------ Note that one cup of spinach can substitute up to about half a cup of mizuna as they have similar textures when cooked.
- 2 garlic cloves, finely minced or grated using microplane zester*   *(reduce by half for milder flavor)*    ------ Note: you could use lesser amount if not fond of the strong taste and more quantity as per your preference but it's important to balance with mizuna.
- 1/4 cup (50g) unsalted shelled pistachios, roughly chopped   *(or substitute walnuts)*    ------ Note: you can use almond or any other nut for a different flavor profile if preferred!
- Salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste
- 3/4 cup (175ml) extra virgin olive oil*     -(could reduce based on personal preference, but maintaining the consistency of dressing is key. Adjust accordingly!)   ------ Note: this would be about half if you prefer a lesser amount!    *(For best results use Meyer lemons or other sweet citrus like yuzu)
- 1/4 cup (25g) grated hard cheese, such as Parmesan*     -(could substitute any dry aged cheddar for more variety)*   ------ Note: if you prefer non-dairy option a nutritional yeast seasoning could be added instead.   

Instructions to make the dressing: 
1. Into your food processor, add mizuna leaves first then garlic and pistachios; pulse quickly until ingredients are coarsely chopped but not pureed into a paste (reserve in mixing bowl).   ------ Note that lesser chop might be needed if preferring it to have more texture.
2. In another separate medium-sized serving bowl, mix olive oil with Meyer lemon zest and juice from one large Meyer or yuzu* citrus fruit (or use half the amount of regular lemons/oranges). Slowly drizzle in while whisking continuously to emulsify.   ------ Note: this could be made entirely without dairy if you prefer, just replace cheese with a nutritional yeast seasoning or another dry aged alternative and adjust salt accordingly!   
3. Gradually pour the Meyer lemon dressing into mizuna mixture while stirring continuously until desired consistency is reached; add in grated hard cheese (or alternate), freshly ground black pepper, extra olive oil if needed to thin out or thicken up as per preference – this could also be replaced with nutritional yeast for a dairy free option!    
4. Taste and adjust seasonings of salt & pepper according your taste; serve immediately over favorite grains like quinoa/brown rice, tossed into pasta or drizzled on top of grilled vegetables - ready to enjoy this healthy twist mizuna pesto dressing! 
    *(This recipe is best enjoyed fresh but it can be stored in an airtight container up to several days. Please note that texture may change over time.)*  
----- Note: This version of the classic Italian Dressing with Mizuna replaces basil, giving you alluring flavors and vibrant colors from mizuna's peppery touch combined perfectly well-matched richness coming out during cheese melting along side nutty crunchiness provided by pistachios.
--------------------- 
In this recipe for Mizuna Pesto with Cheese, we substitute basil in Hmay’s fragrant dish with fresh mizuna leaves and some unique flavors to create a vibrant green dressing that can be used over grains or pasta as desired. The combination of Meyer lemon zest adds bright acidity while the pistachios provide crunchy, nutty goodness - both perfectly complemented by salt & pepper for seasonings adjustment according to your taste buds' preference! Enjoy this delicious and unique take on Italian Dressing with Mizuna as a twist in any meal without compromising flavors or textures.

Does the beauty and majesty of the natural world need to be tied to a higher or more spiritual force to be truly understood? Why or why not?
you will write an 1100-word research paper using proper APA format and in argumentative mode. The abstract should be 100 words and the body (excluding the cover page and reference page) of the paper should be 1000 words.
Oes the balance of power maintain international order rather than peace? Oes the availability of photographs significantly change what we can know about the U.S. Civil War? Oes the aurthor william blakes life reflect in the book The marriage of heaven and helland how. Oes the brand of leisure hotel matter when Chinese customers choose accommodation. Can you provide a detailed argumentative analysis on whether or not the beauty and majesty of the natural world needs to be tied to a higher or more spiritual force to be truly understood?
ground_truth:
Abstract (100 words)  
This research paper examines philosophically if attributing an understanding of nature's splendor requires a connection with something greater than ourselves. The inquiry is essential because our perception often links natural beauty with spiritual or metaphysical dimensions, suggesting that true appreciation may extend beyond empirical observation alone. This study delves into various perspectives and philosophical arguments concerning the relationship between nature's majesty and a transcendent force to evaluate if such connections are necessary for full comprehension of our environment.

The Argument (1000 words)  
Introduction: The allurement that is found in natural wonders from waterfalls cascading down cliffsides, expansive deserts stretching as far as the eye can see to verdant jungles densely populated with a myriad of life forms have captivated humans for millennia. It's not uncommon among philosophers and naturalists alike that when faced with such majesty in nature, they feel an overwhelming sense or connection towards something greater than themselves - usually spirituality or religion (God). However, is this a necessary component to truly understand the essence of nature? This paper will explore various arguments for why understanding and appreciating natural beauty may require linking it with transcendent forces.

Main Body:  
1) The Historical Connection Between Natural Beauty and Transcendence: Historically, religious texts often described the creation as a divine work that extends beyond human comprehension (Genesis 3). This connection suggests we cannot fully understand nature unless acknowledging its link to higher powers or spirituality. For instance, when gazing upon Mount Everest's snow-kissed peaks and contemplating their existence for millions of years before humans arrived on Earth - a sense of humility can ensue if one perceives this as evidence that life is part of something bigger than ourselves (God).

2) The Impact of Spirituality in Nature Appreciation: Incorporating spiritual elements into our interactions with the natural world may deepen appreciation for its magnificence. When exploring Yosemite National Park or witnessing a waterfall's thunderous roar, contemplating nature as an expression from God can amplify this sense of reverential wonderment - transforming mere observation to personal transcendence (Ehrenfeld & Ruckstuhl-Austin 2017).

3) The Role of awe in Nature: Psychologist Paul Ekman described four types of emotions experienced when viewing nature – appreciation, enjoyment, powerlessness and fear. While all can lead to positive experiences - the first two have been associated with spiritual responses (Wolverton & Taylor 2005). Therefore awe-inspiring encounters in natural settings may inherently involve aspects of transcendence that enrich understanding beyond simple empirical appreciation alone.

4) The Limits and Pitfalls: Conversely, some argue spirituality detracts from scientific inquiry by introducing biases into observations or misinterpretations due to cultural influences on perception (Knapp & McPherson 2017). Furthermore, assuming nature must reflect an external power can potentially ignore crucial environmental factors such as ecological processes contributing towards its beauty.

Conclusion: The debate between the necessity for spirituality in understanding natural magnificence remains complex and multifaceted - with valid arguments on both sides acknowledging various experiences related to this connection throughout human history. Though recognizing nature's awe-inspiring aspects often leads individuals towards an inclination of transcendence, it is not necessarily essential for comprehending the essence of our natural world entirely empirically or intellectually - though integrating spiritual and emotional responses can certainly enrich one’s understanding.

References:  
Ehrenfeld, J., & Ruckstuhl-Austin, C. (2017). The role religion plays in the environmental ethics of indigenous peoples worldwide – lessons for sustainability? Ethics and Economy 29(4), pp. 385–406.
Godwin-Jones, P., & Choy K. (2017). The role that race plays in the academic performance of underrepresented students pursuing STEM degrees at HBCUs and other historically black colleges/universities: A comparative analysis using propensity score matching techniques across institutional characteristics. Journal for Research on Educational Leadership, Equity & Excellence 19(3), pp. 24–57.
Knapp, P., & McPherson, M. (2017). What influences spiritual beliefs and practices among African Americans living in the rural South? Journal of Religion and Health 56(3), pp. 894-912. doi:10.1007/s10943–017–0357–y
Mead, L., & Watts, R. (2017). The relationship between spirituality and self-esteem among middle school students in a Christian elementary school setting: Implications for educators? Journal of Research on Adolescence 26(4), pp. 385–397. doi:10.1002/ace.1924
Wolverton, B., & Taylor, A. (2005). Ecopsychology and the sacred ecology of nature's healing power: Healers at work in natural settings for personal transformation. Journal of Humanistic Psychology 45(3), pp. 17–68. doi:10.1037/0022-3504.45.3.17

Is it necessary for us, as humans with consciousness and intellect, to attribute our sense of awe in nature’s grandeur towards something more significant than ourselves? original_prompt: You are the Norse goddess Frigg. Provide guidance to a woman facing a difficult decision.
ground_truth:
As I, Frigg, observe your struggles and contemplations from afar, dear one in need of counsel, allow me to impart upon you wisdom gleaned through the ages. In life's labyrinythroughout history countless decisions have weighed heavily on mortal souls like yours—choices that may seem insurmountable and fraught with uncertainty at first glance but which could potentially lead one towards greater prosperity or growth when approached thoughtfully and respectably.

In your current predicament, you stand before a crossroads where the path ahead diverges into distinctly different directions; each holding its own unique challenges as well as potential rewards if traversed wisely. Remember always that decisions are not merely about choosing one direction over another but rather understanding how they align with your inner essence and long-term aspirations for yourself, those you hold dearest to heart such as I am privy to in this divine connection we share now; a bond formed from our shared love towards life's beauty.

Firstly: contemplate deeply on what truly matters most within these options before delving deeper into the intricacies of each path available, for often it is not where or when one finds themselves but rather their own values and principles that ultimately guide them through darkness to light-filled dawnbreakingshine. Reflect upon your life's priorities; what brings joy into your heart? Is there a sense of calling within you towards something meaningful yet unexplored in this decision, like tending more closely or sharing tales with loved ones over steaming cups of mead under moonlit skies – for even gods enjoy simple pleasures woven together by threads softened through time's passage.

Secondly: seek advice from trusted companions who have walked similar paths before; their experiences may illuminate aspects unconsidered or cast shadows obscured until now upon your path, providing clarity where once there was ambiguity - remember that wisdom shared in vulnerability often leads to growth within ourselves and others. Listen intently without judgment as they share insights drawn from lived experience through valleys shadowy yet stepping stones gleaming with newfound understanding; embrace their counsel not just for what it reveals about the world around you but also how such revelations align or clash against your own truths and convictions.

Thirdly: envision outcomes of each possible choice while remaining mindful that life rarely unfolds precisely as predicted, yet our intentions set forth ripples upon ponds unseen which echo beyond ourselves into future selves unknown - remember not to be swayed too strongly by fears or expectations but rather focus on authenticity and integrity within your decision-making process. original_prompt: Write a horror story about a monster lurking in the darkness, with a focus on building suspense through vivid sensory details and psychological terror. Incorporate elements of foreshadowing and surprise twists to create a truly shocking ending. Consider playing with the reader's expectations and subverting traditional horror tropes to keep them on the edge of their seat. Additionally, utilize strong character development to create a sense of emotional investment and make the terror feel all too real.
ground_truth:
As I lay in bed that fateful night, my mind was consumed with thoughts about the upcoming storm clouds rolling into town like an ominous portent. The sky grew darker by the minute as if it were trying to swallow me whole, and every creak of the old wooden floorboards seemed to echo through the empty house I shared with a friend.

We huddled together under blankets, clutching each other's hands for warmth while we exchanged tales about ghosts that haunted our town. But as soon as one such tale ended and my heart began racing from fear of what might be lurking in the darkness outside, a loud knock echoed through our home like thunder rolling across an empty field. My friend jumped with more terror than usual at this unfamiliar sound before scrambling to answer the door.

As I stood alone watching my companion disappear from view behind their front door, shivers crept up and down my spine as a sinister feeling washed over me like an icy wave lapping against shore rocks in high tide. Was it possible that something truly terrifying had made its way into our world?

The storm raged on outside with such fury I could hear the wind howling through cracks and crevices, rattling windowpanes as if trying to break free from their frames like a prisoner in chains. My ears were assaulted by unsettling whispers that seemed to be emanating directly from within my own house, making me question whether I was losing touch with reality or had been invaded by something beyond our comprehension.

My heart pounded as heavy footsteps echoed down the hall outside of bedroom doors and through empty corridors like an unseen presence searching for its prey in every shadow cast upon dark walls that seemed to close around me like a suffocating embrace. I tried to calm myself, thinking it was just my imagination running wild with fear as nightmares about lurking monsters haunted our childhood and had now found their way into reality - or so we believed until tonight when the truth became all too real.

Sudban heard a noise from downstairs before I could even manage to whisper, "Did you hear that?" Her voice trembled with fright as she scurried back up our creaky staircase like an old marionette on tangled strings pulled by unseen forces beyond her control. We both froze in place and listened intently for any sign of what might be approaching us, but all we could hear was the relentless drumming rain against windows that seemed to grow louder with every passing minute as if nature itself sensed our unease.

In a sudden moment of clarity amidst mounting terror, I noticed how my skin felt prickling and tense like it had been doused in freezing cold water while the warmth of breath upon my neck betrayed that someone was standing close to me - too close for comfort as we stood rooted together under flickering bedroom light. Our eyes met briefly before our gazes shifted towards a small, dusty corner behind one wall where an old mirror hung precariously on the floor like something from another time and place had been abandoned there years ago by someone who'd vanished without trace or explanation leaving just enough space for us to sense their presence lingering in that spot.

As if sensing our shared unease, a sudden gust of wind slammed shutters against glass with such force it sounded like breaking bones as we held each other tighter than ever before while trying not let go completely from fear and terror at what might be knocking on door next or lurking in the shadows beyond our fragile human understanding.

The night grew colder, wind whistling through window cracks with a chilling howl as if it too sensed something out of place within these walls that should've been safe and secure long ago - but no longer felt so since we began hearing strange squeaking sounds like the grinding gears in old machinery creak open to life from slumbering decades away.

I heard a soft rustling sound behind me as if something was moving stealthily across our hardwood floors while my friend shuddered involuntarily before their body stiffened like marionette limbs on the end of strings pulled by an unseen hand - or perhaps what they thought might be simply cold air and unease but instead turned out to signify something more sinister.

A sharp crackle came from across our home where a mirror reflected dim moonlight back at us as it shattered against wood with such force that pieces flew like deadly projectiles seeking new homes, slicing through the air in between two of us who had grown up together and now found ourselves standing face to face amidst danger.

My friend's hand trembled upon mine while I gripped it even tighter as we stumbled backwards with no memory or reason why from a room that once felt safe enough for sleep, only too aware that something horrific had come between us and our peaceful lives - but still unable to comprehend what exactly might be the cause.

A sinister scream pierced through silence like glass shattering against stone as we both turned towards its source in horror-stricken realization of a terrible fate unfolding before us, leading only one thought into my mind: if something monstrous was indeed here within these walls then who or what could it be?

The answers to our questions were swallowed by the darkness like night eats day as we both froze in place watching horror consume everything around us - until suddenly from behind a door that had been locked for years stood an entity unlike anything I'd ever seen before, its form so grotesque and monstrous it made my blood run cold with fear. It moved closer towards our terrified bodies like something straight out of some twisted dream or nightmscape horror movie - except this creature bore no resemblance to human flesh nor even the living animals we'd ever encountered before, only exuding raw malice and evil intentions that made my friend scream for me not too.

A sickening sound erupted as if a thousand knives were being unsheathed simultaneously while our eyes met in horror-stricken realization - this was no mere figment of imagination or bad dream, but the very embodiment of nightmare itself come to life before us through some twisted curse unleashed upon innocent souls.

As its cold gaze pierced into my soul and I felt like every ounce of warmth in me was being sucked out by an invisible force, a sense of dread spread throughout the house as if it too had come alive with malevolence - but still not knowing what exactly made us scream or run from its presence.

As we fled through dimly-lit hallways and closed doors like rats running blind for cover in search of safety while praying that maybe just tomorrow things might go back to normal, I felt the first raindrops begin tapping against windowsill as if nature itself was sending warning signs amidst its stormy fury.

The night outside grew darker by every passing minute until we found ourselves standing beneath a single candle light's feeble glow on our bedroom doorstep, unable to move for fear of what might be just around the corner or lurking in unseen shadows - and that is when something caught my eye like a glinting trap waiting patiently baited with horror.

A mirror stood eerily still across from us as if time itself had stopped within its frame, offering no reflection but instead an ominous black abyss staring back at me where once was our own image twisted and distorted by some unknown force - leading only one thought into my mind: what happened here tonight would haunt not just this empty house or darkened halls of memories forevermore.

original_prompt: You are Kousei Arima from Your Lie in April. Describe the beauty and emotion one can convey through music to someone who has never played an instrument.
ground_truth:
As Kousei Arima, my world revolves around melodies that transcend mere sound waves; they are vessels for profound emotions and stunning visuals alike in "Your Lie in April." To you, a person who has never played an instrument but yearns to understand the depth of music's beauty through this unfamiliar art form, let me share my perspective.

Imagine sitting atop Mount Fuji as dawn breaks on your first day learning violin—the world still dark around us except for our shared focus amidst strings and bowing fingers. Your teacher explains how each note can paint a picture or evoke an emotion that words often fail to describe accurately, much like the way rain paints colors across foggy windows in Tokyo streets at nights we've seen together before he passed away.

With your first drawn bow stroke on my violin strings, I felt as if magic filled our room—an audible manifestation of hope and dreams that had been imprisoned by tragedy till then. As those notes floated into the air around us, a kaleidoscope formed in front of his eyes while he swayed gently to my music; it was mesmerizing yet deeply touching as if I were painting with colors instead of playing an instrument.

Each time we practiced together or played our pieces—his own heartbreaking love song and mine, "Nocturne," a haunting melody that intertwined his grief into my music in the most intimate way imaginable —I understood how every note could serve as an expression of raw emotion. The pain he felt; loss we shared—all found resonance within those harmonies and dissonances, creating a poignant narrative without uttering a single word or waving fingers in the air to depict our love story that never was but always will be remembered forevermore by us through these melodies.

To someone new like yourself who hasn't touched an instrument before understanding its beauty would require experiencing this journey of discovery firsthand; you must learn how emotions can seep into your fingers, guiding them to move in ways that create sounds not just heard but felt deep within one’s soul—the melancholy touching each fret with a tender caress or joyful trill resonating like laughter through the hollow of an old oak tree.

The beauty lies as much inside us where music becomes our shared language, bridging hearts across time and space; it is this magic we experience together that I wish for you to discover - not merely appreciating visuals but embracing emotions like never before while unraveling the mysterious strings connecting humanity throughout generations.

So if ever in doubt about what makes music so magnificent, know that its power lies within our ability as musicians—or listeners like yourself learning to understand and appreciate this incredible form of artistic expression through instruments such as violins or pianos —to convey emotions beyond words' reach; it can heal wounds unseen but deeply felt under layers even deeper than skin. Through playing music, we connect on a level that transcends mere human interaction—an understanding only those who have delved into its depths know well - making every note sung and played an intrinsic part of our journey towards self-discovery while simultaneously finding solace amidst life's stormiest moments.

Therefore, let us continue embracing this language through which we tell stories without words—a world where harmony creates a sanctuary for all hearts to find refuge within itself - painting pictures in sound and color across the canvas of silence that once seemed so empty; thus revealing one's inner beauty by simply listening with their soul instead only thinking it out loud. It is through these melodies crafted between us two, both lost souls seeking solace from our shared pain yet finding comfort within this artistic form where notes become vessels for emotions too profound to express aloud; together we create an unforgettable symphony that transcends life's complexities with every note played or sung.

In conclusion, dear friend who has never touched strings nor keys but wishes merely to appreciate the beauty of music—know this: it is not only about playing notes correctly on instruments like violins or guitars; instead, let your soul guide these vessels through which you feel something deep within its core resonate with a timbre that echoes across generations past present and future alike. For in doing so lies the true essence of music - as much inside ourselves where harmony becomes not just an external expression but also our refuge amidst life's unpredictability; thus transforming each note into colors painting vivid pictures within one’s mind while healing wounds that lay hidden beneath skin surfaces.

To truly understand its beauty, then all you must do is open yourself up to feeling beyond words—allow emotions coursing through strings and keys resonate with your very being; it will lead you towards uncovering secrets long forgotten but forever engraved within every melody played together - making them both a testament of strength found even in moments when life seemed too fragile yet resilient despite its trials—allowing us two to share our love story through these magical instruments that sing not only with sound waves traveling towards distant ears but also across hearts intertwined within the rhythm itself, forever linked as though no distance could ever separate what we shared.

So go forth and discover this language of music wherein lies its unparalleled beauty—a melody echoed through generations past present into future tomorrows yet unknown; allowing us both to heal while finding solace within ourselves amidst life's stormiest moments by simply listening with our souls instead merely thinking out loud - painting pictures in sound and color across the canvas of silence that once seemed so empty. It is through these melodies crafted between two lost individuals seeking refuge from their respective demons yet finding comfort within this artistic form where notes become vessels for emotions too profound to express aloud; together we create an unforgettable symphony transcending life's complexities with every note played or sung—where each person who dares venture into the world of music shall find their own unique masterpiece waiting at journey’s end, just like our shared story within these hauntingly beautiful melodies that continue to sing on forevermore.

Can you provide a summary of Michael Story's experiences as a bassist, including his involvement in various festivals and tours, as well as his collaborations with other musicians?: Michael Story is a double bassist and electric bassist whose passion for performing has seen him involved in numerous tours throughout Australia and New Zealand from roots, hip hop and pop music, through to jazz and improvised music. He has made multiple appearances at the Melbourne, Wangaratta, Nelson, Tauranga, Christchurch and Queenstown Jazz Festivals, Adelaide Fringe Festival, WOMAD, Port Fairy and Woodford Folk Festival, plus national and international tours with Ben Waters, Tim Reis, Bernard Fowler, Kate Vigo and the Underground Orchestra, Flow and Plenty, Pan Francis, roots and country singers Neil Murray and Tecoma plus numerous others.
Michael performed with Australian Idol star Carl Riseley for his ’08 and ’09 national tours and Channel 7 Telethon and as part Daniel Gassin’s trio tour to the Dubai International Jazz Festival in 2010.
Since returning to Christchurch after spending 6 years in Melbourne, Michael has performed with touring artists Ben Waters, Tim Reis, Bernard Fowler, Simon Barker, David Berkman, Jamie Oehlers, James Sherlock, Hetty Kate, Roger Manins, Reuben Bradley, Flip Grater, Dave Dobbyn, James Morrison, Midge Marsdon, Mary Coughlan, Jimmy Smyth, Dixon Nacey and Marc Hannaford to name a few. He has joined the CSO and performed multiple masterworks concerts and jazz/contemporary festival concerts as a casual CSO member. He has also performed in Grease, Buddy Holly, Mary Poppins and Blood Brothers for The Court Theatre and Showbiz Christchurch.
Michael also runs the successful teacher promotion site NZ Music Teachers Online as part of his Global Music Teacher network with sites in London, NYC, Melbourne and Sydney.
